p.k: Follow the lives of orphaned orangutan babies as they are brought to the world’s oldest orangutan sanctuary in Borneo. Toddlers are wheel-barrowed in for lessons in life
One orphan is new on the scene, and needs another, more experienced one to help them bed in. The babies are at high risk from parasites ingested from the ground
The orphaned orangutan Peanut is one of the newest and youngest arrivals at the sanctuary. He has made friends with Beryl, but he is not feeling very well
Jack Yabsley and the HMS Buccaneer count down the ten stinkiest animal on the planet. With their ‘Stinkometer-4000’ they’ll analyse animal aromas
Jack and the Buccaneer count down the top ten ‘bites’ of the animal world. They’ll calculate each animals jaw strength to rank the best
Jack and Buck compare the world’s top ten wackiest animal racers with human sprinters. Could a monkey outrun the world’s fastest man?
As temperatures reach over 110 degrees, medical technician Stacie Dabolt is called in to rescue two dogs trapped in the glare of the midday sun
The team makes a dramatic rescue when a spaniel gets trapped underground. Plus, a challenging situation arises when a dog and her pups are attacked by bees
It's a race against time as an AHS team battle to save a kitten trapped in a maze of underground pipes. A dog with a fatal injury is the centre of a shocking case
A puppy is rescued from a kill shelter in Oklahoma. And a dog eats a box of toxic chocolates infused with marijuana, and is rushed to the clinic for treatment
Dr Jeff races to save the legs of a puppy who has been hit by a car. And newly hired exotic pet vet, Dr Baier, treats a Burmese python that is losing weight
With thousands of animals in need, and vet care unaffordable to most, Dr Jeff heads to Mexico to run a mobile clinic and help as many people and pets as they can
Dr Jeff fights to save a bearded dragon which is having a seizure, and Dr Amy is put to the test when a routine cat neuter turns complicated

p.n: Coyote Peterson: Return To The Wilderness
p.k: Coyote Peterson and his crew plunge deep on a dangerous journey into the Costa Rican rainforest where they find Central America’s most lethal pit viper
Coyote heads to Texas in search of a rumoured giant snapping turtle. He is determined to prove that this turtle is the largest living creature of his kind
Coyote heads to Brazil to encounter the Yacare Caiman. As he swims alongside them in piranha-infested waterways, he studies their perfect-predator personality
Capturing big cats on film is a near-impossible task, but Coyote demonstrates how with technology nature enthusiasts can see predators like jaguars up close
Animal expert Coyote Peterson navigates the turbulent waters of Australia’s tidepools at night to find and get close to the elusive wobbegong sharks
Animal expert Coyote Peterson explores the inner tidepools along Australia’s Sunshine Coast to find and get close to its venomous marine creatures
Jackson observes a group of five cheetahs cooperatively hunting. Meanwhile, Jonathan witnesses a spectacular river crossing of thousands of wildebeest
Indonesia is home to more active volcanoes than any other country on earth. How has the wildlife here uniquely adapted to the specific demands of life in the furnace?
New evidence reveals a Vietnam War pilot may have returned home with a secret cargo. Experts use this to try and find the missing link in human evolution
40% The team is back to Louisiana to investigate a photo of a possible Sasquatch. With the help of a local drum line, they hope to lure the beast of the bayou
40% The team travels to the Blue Mountains to meet with local anthropologist Professor Jeff Meldrum who discovered the tracks of a possible Bigfoot
40% The team travels to Bobo's backyard to investigate photos of a possible Bigfoot among the Redwoods. Will using heavy metal vocals work as bait?
40% Four eccentric but passionate Bigfoot enthusiasts embark on one single-minded mission: to find the elusive "creature" known as Bigfoot
40% The team travels to Nepal in search of the infamous Yeti. They visit monasteries to examine relics and travel into the dense forests of the Himalayas
40% The team travels to Idaho, and after sending a scout team of researchers ahead of the group, they split into teams and disperse across the state
Animals can do extraordinary things – but how do they do it? Experts spill the secrets of the animal kingdom with amazing footage and surprising facts
